                           <div class="detaildropdown-content">
                                                                                          <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>What is the best time to visit Ranthan Kharak trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p>
The best seasons are May to June (spring) and September to early November (post-monsoon) when weather conditions are stable and views are clear.<br /></p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>How difficult is the Ranthan Kharak trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p>

The trek is rated as moderate difficulty. It’s suitable for beginners with good fitness levels as well as experienced trekkers. Day 5 is the most challenging with a 14.2 km distance and significant elevation change.<br /></p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>What is the total Ranthan Kharak trek distance?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p>

The total trekking distance is approximately 38 km, spread over 5 trekking days.<br /></p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>Is there an age restriction for this trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p>

Himalayan Hikers recommends an age range of 12 to 62 years for this trek, though exceptions can be made based on fitness levels and previous trekking experience.<br /></p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>Is the Ranthan Kharak trek suitable for first-time trekkers?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p>

Yes, with adequate physical preparation and basic fitness. However, having some prior trekking experience, even on easier trails, would be beneficial<br /></p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>Are there any ATMs or network connectivity during the trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p>

No, there are no ATMs on the trail, and network connectivity is extremely limited. It’s advisable to carry sufficient cash and inform family about limited connectivity before departing.<br /></p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>Do we need to carry our own sleeping bags?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p>

When booking with Himalayan Hikers, sleeping bags and mattresses are provided as part of the package. However, you may bring your own if you prefer.<br /></p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                                                       </div>
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
